# Terminal Rendering + Agent DX Research

## Terminal Table Rendering Crates

| Crate | Downloads | MD Input? | API | Best For |
|-------|-----------|-----------|-----|----------|
| termimad | 33K | Yes | Template | Render existing markdown pipe tables directly |
| comfy-table | 53M | No | Builder | Most mature, best wrapping algorithm |
| tabled | 20M | No | Derive | Cleanest struct-to-table via #[derive(Tabled)] |
| cli-table | 3.8M | No | Derive | Middle ground |
| prettytable-rs | 3.3K | No | Builder | Declining, skip |

### Recommendation: termimad

Since clap_describe already outputs markdown with pipe tables, termimad can render it directly to formatted ASCII table with colors + auto terminal width. Zero data transformation needed.

Fallback: comfy-table if more layout control needed.

### termimad key features
- Direct markdown support with pipe table rendering
- Dynamic table width detection and wrapping
- Colored output with adaptive skins (light/dark detection)
- TextTemplate system for data expansion
- Supports pipe-delimited markdown tables with alignment

## googleworkspace/cli Agent DX Patterns

### Their schema command
- `gws schema drive.files.list` — dotted-path introspection, JSON-only
- `--resolve-refs` flag inlines nested schemas
- Auto-generated SKILL.md files with YAML frontmatter for LLM consumption
- `--dry-run` flag for agent safety (validate without executing)
- MCP server mode (`gws mcp`) for direct LLM tool registration

### SKILL.md format
```yaml
---
name: gws-docs-write
version: 1.0.0
description: Append text to Google Docs
metadata.openclaw:
  category: productivity
  requires.bins: gws
  cliHelp: gws docs +write --help
---
# docs +write
## Prerequisite
## Description
## Usage
## Flags
## Examples
## Tips
## See Also
```

### Patterns worth adopting in clap_describe

| Pattern | Priority | Description |
|---------|----------|-------------|
| SKILL.md generation | High | Auto-generate agent skill files from --describe |
| --dry-run | Medium | Validate CLI construction without side effects |
| MCP-compatible output | Medium | Schema format mapping to MCP tool definitions |
| Dotted path discovery | Low | md-fme describe enforce.folder for arg-level introspection |

### Broader ecosystem trends (2025-2026)
- JSON output as default for agent-facing commands
- Schema-first CLI design gaining traction
- MCP becoming standard agent-tool protocol
- --help output doubling as tool description for LLMs

